snippet.textDisplay:
What an absolutely beautiful rendition of Sohni-Mahival story, a fable which has been such an integral part of growing up all these years!
And, wow! Shilpa Rao in coke studio pk. While the fascist propaganda continues to show Pakistan and India as hell , and the fanatics from both side continue to blame each other, our music which is invariably intertwined continues to transcend all boundaries.
Channa or Chenab arises as confluence of two ethereal Himalayan rivers; Chandra and Bhaga. They both start near Baralacha La and trace opposite directions and yet come to meet each other at Tandi in Lahaul and go on further and enter Pakistan . Our rivers and destinies are interlinked and so are our stories. Some day, this separation might just come full circle like the love story of Chandra and Bhaga. We're all one. Some day, we all might learn this. It's a folly to give up on such a beautiful hope.  :)
